== 迴響 ==

=== 評價 ===
Despite a strong critical start for the third season premiere, the season received more negative reviews than the previous seasons.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/arrow/s03/ |title=Arrow: Season 3 |date=2014-10-08 |publisher=rottentomatoes.com |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150610103428/http://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/arrow/s03/ |archive-date=2015-06-10 |language=en-US}}</ref>

Writing for [[Entertainment_Weekly|Entertainment Weekly]], Chancellor Agard noted that season had been an uneven one where the "highs have been rather high and the lows have been almost insufferable" and highlighted that the season' biggest problem seemed to lie in the characterisation and motivation of the season's big bad, [[Ra's_al_Ghul_(Arrowverse)|Ra's al Ghul]]. He did however praise the development of the character [[Laurel_Lance_(Arrowverse)|Laurel Lance]] as well as the development of Oliver's relationship with [[John_Diggle_(Arrowverse)|John Diggle]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/recap/arrow-season-3-finale/3/|title=Arrow season 3 finale recap: My Name is Oliver Queen|last=Agard|first=Chancellor|work=[[Entertainment_Weekly|Entertainment Weekly]]|date=2015-05-14|access-date=2018-07-09|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170803164547/http://ew.com/recap/arrow-season-3-finale/3/|archive-date=2017-08-03|language=en-US}}</ref>

Katie Kulzick, of [[The_A.V._Club|A.V. Club]] noted that the season had a habit of "making bold moves and all too frequently backing away from, rather than embracing, the ramifications of these series-altering decisions." Despite the season's "significant problems", she felt groundwork had been laid for interesting potential storylines, in particular the development of [[Thea_Queen|Thea Queen]] becoming a member of the team as Speedy, for [[Felicity_Smoak_(Arrowverse)|Felicity Smoak]] with Palmer Technologies and for Oliver to develop a fresh perspective.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tv.avclub.com/arrow-my-name-is-oliver-queen-1798183796|title=Arrow: "My Name Is Oliver Queen"|last=Kulzick|first=Kate|work=[[The_A.V._Club|The A.V. Club]]|date=2018-05-14|access-date=2018-07-09|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170827090032/http://tv.avclub.com/arrow-my-name-is-oliver-queen-1798183796|archive-date=2017-08-27|language=en-US}}</ref>

The season finale was described as "dull", "lacking scope", and "underwhelming" by IGN's Jesse Schedeen in light of the "high standard" the show had previously established for its finales. He cemented the mixed reception of the third season as being "haphazardly paced" and "struggling to develop a clear sense of direction".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://au.ign.com/articles/2015/05/20/arrow-season-3-review |title=Arrow: Season 3 Review |last=Schedeen |first=Jesse |date=2015-05-20 |work=[[IGN|IGN]] |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171202180949/http://au.ign.com/articles/2015/05/20/arrow-season-3-review |archive-date=2017-12-02 |language=en-US}}</ref>

The third season holds a score of 90% on Rotten Tomatoes based on 9 reviews, with an average rating of 8.37/10. The site's consensus concluding: "''Arrow'' stays on target with new characters and a steady supply of exciting action."<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/arrow/s03|title=Arrow: Season 3 – Rotten Tomatoes|access-date=2018-05-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171129070101/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/arrow/s03/|archive-date=2017-11-29|dead-url=no|language=en-US}}</ref>

